WEBVTT

00:07:59.411 --> 00:08:00.912
Like a writer who said,

00:08:00.936 --> 00:08:02.534
SA: "You need to do something

00:08:02.558 --> 00:08:05.756
to make sure you're actually
getting the work done."

00:08:05.780 --> 00:08:10.612
And even though his work
was very creative, he said,

00:08:10.636 --> 00:08:15.160
"One way that makes sense to me
is to do it like a bricklayer."

00:08:15.614 --> 00:08:19.583
You know, that you need to lay
a certain number of bricks every day.

00:08:19.607 --> 00:08:24.691
He found he had to put himself
into that mode of productivity

00:08:24.715 --> 00:08:27.730
rather than chasing creativity.

00:08:28.199 --> 00:08:30.770
AG: The third structure
was ongoing interaction: